Description: Fragment of double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine brick red; cream slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and second stamp with club symbol.
Curator's comments: Name, Philinos. Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.110, 41. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0151)
